{"word":"ἄφθεγκτος","slug":"ἄφθεγκτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄφθεγκτος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φθέγγομαι'><el>φθέγγομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>voiceless</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of places, <i>where none may speak</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>unspeakable</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}